This article is a transcript of a speech given by Vice President Kamala Harris at an event commemorating the passing of the bipartisan Safer Communities Act, which aims to address gun violence in the United States. Harris emphasizes the importance of this legislation and discusses her personal commitment to tackling gun violence throughout her career. She also praises President Joe Biden for his longstanding efforts in advocating for gun control measures and highlights his past achievements in passing the Brady Handgun Violence Prevention Act and a ban on assault weapons and high-capacity magazines. The Vice President concludes by introducing Garnell Whitfield, Jr., a guest who has lost his mother to gun violence.